WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.470 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.470 --> 00:00:30.180 align:middle line:90%


00:00:30.180 --> 00:00:33.620 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you have
stress in your life?

00:00:33.620 --> 00:00:35.980 align:middle line:84%
I bet you do, because
most of us do.

00:00:35.980 --> 00:00:40.330 align:middle line:84%
As a matter of fact, stress
is the number one killer

00:00:40.330 --> 00:00:41.890 align:middle line:90%
in the United States today.

00:00:41.890 --> 00:00:45.580 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to talk
to a motivational speaker

00:00:45.580 --> 00:00:50.830 align:middle line:84%
and a trainer today who
had some of the answers

00:00:50.830 --> 00:00:53.590 align:middle line:84%
on how we can deal with
the stress in our life.

00:00:53.590 --> 00:00:56.610 align:middle line:84%
I'd like to introduce
you to Celeste Johnson.

00:00:56.610 --> 00:00:57.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Hi.

00:00:57.610 --> 00:00:59.740 align:middle line:90%
>> Glad to have you here.

00:00:59.740 --> 00:01:02.800 align:middle line:84%
Your program is called
"The Balancing Act."

00:01:02.800 --> 00:01:06.760 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's a very
interesting term, the balancing

00:01:06.760 --> 00:01:07.900 align:middle line:90%
act.

00:01:07.900 --> 00:01:09.520 align:middle line:90%
What does that mean to you?

00:01:09.520 --> 00:01:12.730 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, it means being able to
juggle the myriad of demands

00:01:12.730 --> 00:01:14.650 align:middle line:84%
that we have, and the
desires that we have.

00:01:14.650 --> 00:01:18.730 align:middle line:84%
And how do you juggle those
things and not drop the ball,

00:01:18.730 --> 00:01:21.160 align:middle line:84%
or have some balance
in your life?

00:01:21.160 --> 00:01:22.630 align:middle line:84%
And it's so
important to do that.

00:01:22.630 --> 00:01:25.450 align:middle line:90%
And I think it's really an art.

00:01:25.450 --> 00:01:26.600 align:middle line:90%
It's an art.

00:01:26.600 --> 00:01:28.300 align:middle line:84%
It's a skill that
you have to develop.

00:01:28.300 --> 00:01:29.840 align:middle line:90%
And we all are facing it.

00:01:29.840 --> 00:01:31.510 align:middle line:84%
We're all facing
the situations where

00:01:31.510 --> 00:01:33.610 align:middle line:90%
we have too much on our plate.

00:01:33.610 --> 00:01:35.260 align:middle line:90%
Things are changing so fast.

00:01:35.260 --> 00:01:37.300 align:middle line:10%
We're all feeling
remnants of Stress--

00:01:37.300 --> 00:01:38.950 align:middle line:10%
in capital letters.

00:01:38.950 --> 00:01:40.570 align:middle line:10%
And what we have
to do is to learn

00:01:40.570 --> 00:01:42.080 align:middle line:10%
how to take those components--

00:01:42.080 --> 00:01:44.080 align:middle line:10%
those components are
important, those components

00:01:44.080 --> 00:01:47.350 align:middle line:10%
that are not important, decipher
which they are, and then

00:01:47.350 --> 00:01:48.150 align:middle line:10%
have some balance.

00:01:48.150 --> 00:01:50.442 align:middle line:84%
And have some enjoyment, so
we're enjoying life and not

00:01:50.442 --> 00:01:53.080 align:middle line:84%
just going through life on what
I call the proverbial treadmill

00:01:53.080 --> 00:01:54.670 align:middle line:90%
of life.

00:01:54.670 --> 00:01:58.690 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you think women are more
apt to have stress and balance

00:01:58.690 --> 00:02:01.720 align:middle line:84%
in their life, and trouble with
balancing their life, than men?

00:02:01.720 --> 00:02:02.620 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:02:02.620 --> 00:02:06.010 align:middle line:84%
And I think it
really goes back to,

00:02:06.010 --> 00:02:08.110 align:middle line:84%
I guess, the stereotypes
in some of the systems

00:02:08.110 --> 00:02:09.882 align:middle line:84%
that we had of old,
where women were

00:02:09.882 --> 00:02:12.340 align:middle line:84%
expected to do the things in
the home-- the typical things.

00:02:12.340 --> 00:02:15.820 align:middle line:84%
Even though we're in the '90s
and we do have a lot of women

00:02:15.820 --> 00:02:18.520 align:middle line:84%
out there in the workforce,
still, a lot of people

00:02:18.520 --> 00:02:21.190 align:middle line:84%
expect women to continue to
do all of the same things they

00:02:21.190 --> 00:02:22.450 align:middle line:90%
did before in the home.

00:02:22.450 --> 00:02:24.730 align:middle line:84%
Take care of the children,
do the grocery shopping,

00:02:24.730 --> 00:02:27.490 align:middle line:84%
et cetera, and work a full-time
job and do all of the things

00:02:27.490 --> 00:02:30.440 align:middle line:84%
that, typically, the
male would do so.

00:02:30.440 --> 00:02:34.038 align:middle line:84%
And I think women themselves
still feel that responsibility.

00:02:34.038 --> 00:02:36.580 align:middle line:84%
And occasionally, you'll have
a spouse, or friend, or someone

00:02:36.580 --> 00:02:38.020 align:middle line:90%
else that will help you there.

00:02:38.020 --> 00:02:40.300 align:middle line:84%
But I think that women
still internalize the fact

00:02:40.300 --> 00:02:42.940 align:middle line:84%
that I should be the caretaker,
and I've got to do it all.

00:02:42.940 --> 00:02:45.260 align:middle line:84%
And our society tells
us, you can have it all.

00:02:45.260 --> 00:02:46.060 align:middle line:90%
You can do it all.

00:02:46.060 --> 00:02:47.580 align:middle line:90%
And we believe it.

00:02:47.580 --> 00:02:49.210 align:middle line:84%
And we're out there
trying to do it.

00:02:49.210 --> 00:02:52.510 align:middle line:84%
And we find ourselves
just feeling burnt out,

00:02:52.510 --> 00:02:55.352 align:middle line:84%
which is where I say is
the ultimate stress--

00:02:55.352 --> 00:02:56.560 align:middle line:90%
is really getting burned out.

00:02:56.560 --> 00:02:59.200 align:middle line:84%
>> And you said "a lot
of people" seem to think.

00:02:59.200 --> 00:03:00.990 align:middle line:90%
Are you talking about men?

00:03:00.990 --> 00:03:02.860 align:middle line:84%
>> Actually, I think
it's across the board.

00:03:02.860 --> 00:03:04.790 align:middle line:90%
I think men a lot--

00:03:04.790 --> 00:03:05.590 align:middle line:90%
more so than women.

00:03:05.590 --> 00:03:09.790 align:middle line:84%
>> You think men expect women
to be the caretakers in the home

00:03:09.790 --> 00:03:11.020 align:middle line:90%
and work a full-time job?

00:03:11.020 --> 00:03:12.070 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:03:12.070 --> 00:03:13.120 align:middle line:90%
Most of them.

00:03:13.120 --> 00:03:15.280 align:middle line:84%
I do have some friends
in mind that I've

00:03:15.280 --> 00:03:17.800 align:middle line:84%
experienced a little
different, but that's a rarity.

00:03:17.800 --> 00:03:21.010 align:middle line:84%
I usually don't find
a lot of men who--

00:03:21.010 --> 00:03:23.860 align:middle line:84%
wife may be involved with the
workforce in whatever degree,

00:03:23.860 --> 00:03:25.870 align:middle line:90%
some more involved in others.

00:03:25.870 --> 00:03:28.420 align:middle line:84%
But they still expect
her to come home

00:03:28.420 --> 00:03:29.950 align:middle line:84%
and do some of the
domestic things--

00:03:29.950 --> 00:03:31.180 align:middle line:90%
many of the domestic things.

00:03:31.180 --> 00:03:33.320 align:middle line:84%
Or at least arrange
to get them done.

00:03:33.320 --> 00:03:35.320 align:middle line:84%
Even if she's not the one
that actually does it,

00:03:35.320 --> 00:03:36.612 align:middle line:90%
she would just take care of it.

00:03:36.612 --> 00:03:38.350 align:middle line:84%
It's not even part of
their consciousness

00:03:38.350 --> 00:03:40.000 align:middle line:90%
to have to deal with that.

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:41.470 align:middle line:90%
>> So we have a second shift.

00:03:41.470 --> 00:03:41.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:03:41.710 --> 00:03:42.668 align:middle line:90%
>> And the first shift.

00:03:42.668 --> 00:03:43.535 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:03:43.535 --> 00:03:44.410 align:middle line:90%
First, second, third.

00:03:44.410 --> 00:03:46.000 align:middle line:84%
>> What got you
interested in this?

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:48.020 align:middle line:84%
>> In the balancing
act in particular?

00:03:48.020 --> 00:03:50.800 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I tell you, I lived it.

00:03:50.800 --> 00:03:53.320 align:middle line:84%
I tell you, I used to
work very closely--

00:03:53.320 --> 00:03:56.680 align:middle line:84%
I still do-- with a
motivational speaker, Les Brown.

00:03:56.680 --> 00:03:59.050 align:middle line:90%
And I love this industry.

00:03:59.050 --> 00:04:00.250 align:middle line:90%
I love what we do.

00:04:00.250 --> 00:04:02.770 align:middle line:84%
And we got together
to do some projects.

00:04:02.770 --> 00:04:05.290 align:middle line:84%
Well, I always have
this attitude--

00:04:05.290 --> 00:04:08.140 align:middle line:84%
this can-do attitude,
and "I can do this."

00:04:08.140 --> 00:04:10.060 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't control
that very well.

00:04:10.060 --> 00:04:13.480 align:middle line:84%
So as different projects and
responsibilities would come up,

00:04:13.480 --> 00:04:14.980 align:middle line:84%
I would say, oh,
yes, I can do that.

00:04:14.980 --> 00:04:15.490 align:middle line:90%
No problem.

00:04:15.490 --> 00:04:17.260 align:middle line:84%
I'll just cut back
on my sleep, right?

00:04:17.260 --> 00:04:19.600 align:middle line:84%
And another project or
another problem will come up.

00:04:19.600 --> 00:04:20.740 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I can handle that too.

00:04:20.740 --> 00:04:23.420 align:middle line:84%
The can-do attitude
can get you in trouble.

00:04:23.420 --> 00:04:25.630 align:middle line:84%
So I just kept on taking
on other responsibilities,

00:04:25.630 --> 00:04:28.030 align:middle line:84%
and more and more, until
it was a point where

00:04:28.030 --> 00:04:32.470 align:middle line:84%
either your body shuts down
or you just get so exhausted.

00:04:32.470 --> 00:04:34.210 align:middle line:90%
And that's what I experienced--

00:04:34.210 --> 00:04:36.487 align:middle line:84%
that I wasn't
having fun anymore.

00:04:36.487 --> 00:04:37.570 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't enjoying my life.

00:04:37.570 --> 00:04:40.765 align:middle line:84%
Before I knew it, years
was passing-- literally.

00:04:40.765 --> 00:04:42.640 align:middle line:84%
And I wasn't keeping in
touch with my family.

00:04:42.640 --> 00:04:45.130 align:middle line:84%
I know many of our
viewers have forgotten

00:04:45.130 --> 00:04:46.930 align:middle line:84%
to send birthday
cards, greeting cards,

00:04:46.930 --> 00:04:48.550 align:middle line:90%
to your family and friends.

00:04:48.550 --> 00:04:52.240 align:middle line:84%
I had Christmas cards
that I still have.

00:04:52.240 --> 00:04:53.120 align:middle line:90%
>> From years ago.

00:04:53.120 --> 00:04:54.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Years ago.

00:04:54.530 --> 00:04:57.160 align:middle line:84%
And just never got around to
those things that connect you

00:04:57.160 --> 00:05:00.040 align:middle line:84%
to people, connect you to the
things that are important.

00:05:00.040 --> 00:05:02.500 align:middle line:84%
And I think you just kind of
get going, and you get going.

00:05:02.500 --> 00:05:04.850 align:middle line:90%
And I felt very burnt out.

00:05:04.850 --> 00:05:08.170 align:middle line:84%
And I got to the point
for me where it really

00:05:08.170 --> 00:05:10.030 align:middle line:90%
didn't matter what happened.

00:05:10.030 --> 00:05:11.350 align:middle line:90%
If I took off--

00:05:11.350 --> 00:05:12.290 align:middle line:90%
I had to take off.

00:05:12.290 --> 00:05:13.420 align:middle line:90%
I had to get away.

00:05:13.420 --> 00:05:15.095 align:middle line:90%
Because I knew I was losing me.

00:05:15.095 --> 00:05:16.970 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't see me in
the midst of it anymore.

00:05:16.970 --> 00:05:18.445 align:middle line:90%
I only saw work.

00:05:18.445 --> 00:05:20.320 align:middle line:84%
Even though it was good,
and it was fruitful,

00:05:20.320 --> 00:05:22.090 align:middle line:84%
and it was helping
others, there is

00:05:22.090 --> 00:05:24.070 align:middle line:84%
a point when you have
to make sure you're

00:05:24.070 --> 00:05:25.630 align:middle line:90%
being true to yourself.

00:05:25.630 --> 00:05:28.780 align:middle line:84%
And we are so busy,
we don't have time

00:05:28.780 --> 00:05:31.770 align:middle line:84%
to enjoy what we're
saying we're busy for.

00:05:31.770 --> 00:05:33.560 align:middle line:84%
And I see a of people
who say, I want

00:05:33.560 --> 00:05:36.260 align:middle line:84%
to work a little harder so
my kids can have the better

00:05:36.260 --> 00:05:38.450 align:middle line:84%
things, and they can go
to the better schools,

00:05:38.450 --> 00:05:40.880 align:middle line:84%
and we can wear the clothes--
and again, our society

00:05:40.880 --> 00:05:42.260 align:middle line:90%
feeds into that.

00:05:42.260 --> 00:05:43.710 align:middle line:90%
We say, you can have it all.

00:05:43.710 --> 00:05:46.220 align:middle line:84%
You can-- sure, just charge
it, or whatever it is.

00:05:46.220 --> 00:05:47.660 align:middle line:90%
Just work an extra weekend.

00:05:47.660 --> 00:05:49.850 align:middle line:84%
But we have the children--
they have the gym

00:05:49.850 --> 00:05:52.370 align:middle line:84%
shoes, the wonderful
ones that cost $150 plus,

00:05:52.370 --> 00:05:55.090 align:middle line:84%
but we don't have time to
watch them play in them.

00:05:55.090 --> 00:05:57.020 align:middle line:90%
And then-- so what is it for?

00:05:57.020 --> 00:05:59.570 align:middle line:84%
And my question always
is, have we given up

00:05:59.570 --> 00:06:02.060 align:middle line:90%
too much to have it all?

00:06:02.060 --> 00:06:04.110 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, your tape
program and your--

00:06:04.110 --> 00:06:06.110 align:middle line:84%
I think it's quite
interesting, because you also

00:06:06.110 --> 00:06:06.980 align:middle line:90%
have a workbook.

00:06:06.980 --> 00:06:07.640 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:06:07.640 --> 00:06:08.440 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:06:08.440 --> 00:06:11.600 align:middle line:84%
>> So that people can actually
do the exercises that you give

00:06:11.600 --> 00:06:13.460 align:middle line:90%
them on the tape.

00:06:13.460 --> 00:06:19.140 align:middle line:84%
But some of these suggestions
you're giving are so basic,

00:06:19.140 --> 00:06:21.050 align:middle line:90%
but we tend to forget them.

00:06:21.050 --> 00:06:21.890 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:06:21.890 --> 00:06:22.420 align:middle line:90%
And I think that's what we do.

00:06:22.420 --> 00:06:23.220 align:middle line:90%
>> Like the one.

00:06:23.220 --> 00:06:24.200 align:middle line:90%
The one.

00:06:24.200 --> 00:06:27.770 align:middle line:84%
That it's so basic that
we forget about is,

00:06:27.770 --> 00:06:29.270 align:middle line:90%
learn how to say no.

00:06:29.270 --> 00:06:30.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Hello.

00:06:30.710 --> 00:06:31.740 align:middle line:90%
That's me.

00:06:31.740 --> 00:06:32.540 align:middle line:90%
Didn't do it.

00:06:32.540 --> 00:06:34.130 align:middle line:84%
I know, we don't--
they are so basic.

00:06:34.130 --> 00:06:35.670 align:middle line:90%
You mentioned that it is simple.

00:06:35.670 --> 00:06:38.990 align:middle line:84%
The real nuggets of
wisdom is simple.

00:06:38.990 --> 00:06:40.240 align:middle line:90%
They're simple.

00:06:40.240 --> 00:06:41.270 align:middle line:90%
Yet we can't do them.

00:06:41.270 --> 00:06:42.560 align:middle line:84%
We find them difficult.
We are looking

00:06:42.560 --> 00:06:43.790 align:middle line:90%
for the complicated answer.

00:06:43.790 --> 00:06:44.870 align:middle line:90%
It's like, just be quiet.

00:06:44.870 --> 00:06:46.487 align:middle line:90%
Just say no.

00:06:46.487 --> 00:06:47.320 align:middle line:90%
The whole campaign--

00:06:47.320 --> 00:06:48.170 align:middle line:90%
>> And you said, say it early.

00:06:48.170 --> 00:06:49.070 align:middle line:90%
>> Say it very early.

00:06:49.070 --> 00:06:50.250 align:middle line:90%
Say it early, say it firmly.

00:06:50.250 --> 00:06:51.050 align:middle line:90%
And just--

00:06:51.050 --> 00:06:51.920 align:middle line:90%
>> And don't say maybe.

00:06:51.920 --> 00:06:52.520 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:06:52.520 --> 00:06:53.600 align:middle line:84%
Because you build
up their hopes.

00:06:53.600 --> 00:06:54.800 align:middle line:84%
And people think that maybe
they're going to come.

00:06:54.800 --> 00:06:57.770 align:middle line:84%
And then it's harder later
on to come back and say no,

00:06:57.770 --> 00:06:59.890 align:middle line:84%
whereas if you say no
and you're able to do it,

00:06:59.890 --> 00:07:02.960 align:middle line:84%
it would be a nice surprise,
and they'll be happy.

00:07:02.960 --> 00:07:06.755 align:middle line:84%
But I think that it's real
important that we just--

00:07:06.755 --> 00:07:07.880 align:middle line:90%
absolutely doesn't do that.

00:07:07.880 --> 00:07:10.160 align:middle line:84%
But let me tell you what
I think really works best,

00:07:10.160 --> 00:07:12.740 align:middle line:84%
and how you can get to the
point where you can say no

00:07:12.740 --> 00:07:15.080 align:middle line:84%
and it feels OK, or a
little bit more comfortable.

00:07:15.080 --> 00:07:18.170 align:middle line:84%
If we are clear of
what our goals are,

00:07:18.170 --> 00:07:20.430 align:middle line:84%
and what our values
are, and our purpose,

00:07:20.430 --> 00:07:22.490 align:middle line:84%
I think that's really
the root of getting away

00:07:22.490 --> 00:07:23.810 align:middle line:90%
from some of the stresses.

00:07:23.810 --> 00:07:26.750 align:middle line:84%
Because if you're clear what's
important, who's important,

00:07:26.750 --> 00:07:29.180 align:middle line:84%
where you're headed, then
it's like a framework

00:07:29.180 --> 00:07:31.940 align:middle line:84%
that gives you something
to say yes or no,

00:07:31.940 --> 00:07:33.295 align:middle line:90%
if it fits or doesn't fit.

00:07:33.295 --> 00:07:34.670 align:middle line:84%
But if you're not
clear of that--

00:07:34.670 --> 00:07:36.262 align:middle line:90%
which most people are not--

00:07:36.262 --> 00:07:37.970 align:middle line:84%
then it's easy to take
on something else,

00:07:37.970 --> 00:07:39.080 align:middle line:90%
because we don't know.

00:07:39.080 --> 00:07:39.980 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't fit.

00:07:39.980 --> 00:07:40.820 align:middle line:90%
Or it might fit.

00:07:40.820 --> 00:07:42.485 align:middle line:84%
Or we just do it because
we have no system.

00:07:42.485 --> 00:07:43.550 align:middle line:90%
>> We don't know how to say no.

00:07:43.550 --> 00:07:44.480 align:middle line:90%
We're afraid to say no.

00:07:44.480 --> 00:07:45.140 align:middle line:90%
>> That's true.

00:07:45.140 --> 00:07:46.100 align:middle line:84%
That's true,
because-- That's true.

00:07:46.100 --> 00:07:47.450 align:middle line:90%
You don't want to let them down.

00:07:47.450 --> 00:07:49.280 align:middle line:84%
We feel like we have
to try to do this.

00:07:49.280 --> 00:07:50.777 align:middle line:84%
But if we continue
to do that, we

00:07:50.777 --> 00:07:52.610 align:middle line:84%
get to that point where
we're talking about,

00:07:52.610 --> 00:07:53.510 align:middle line:90%
getting burnt out.

00:07:53.510 --> 00:07:55.370 align:middle line:90%
And then you have to say no.

00:07:55.370 --> 00:07:56.770 align:middle line:90%
We talked about--

00:07:56.770 --> 00:07:58.910 align:middle line:84%
Les and I, many
times, talk about how,

00:07:58.910 --> 00:08:03.190 align:middle line:84%
unfortunately, people wait
until they either get sick--

00:08:03.190 --> 00:08:03.990 align:middle line:90%
you get the flu.

00:08:03.990 --> 00:08:05.390 align:middle line:84%
You know how you work,
and you work, and then

00:08:05.390 --> 00:08:06.432 align:middle line:90%
suddenly you're laid out?

00:08:06.432 --> 00:08:07.568 align:middle line:90%
You can't do anything else?

00:08:07.568 --> 00:08:09.110 align:middle line:84%
Because we've
overextended ourselves.

00:08:09.110 --> 00:08:10.568 align:middle line:84%
We haven't taken
care of ourselves.

00:08:10.568 --> 00:08:14.570 align:middle line:84%
Or some medical condition
that just shakes us up.

00:08:14.570 --> 00:08:16.730 align:middle line:84%
And then we start looking
at the things that

00:08:16.730 --> 00:08:19.040 align:middle line:84%
will keep us in balance
and keep us in order.

00:08:19.040 --> 00:08:21.500 align:middle line:84%
But we shouldn't have
to wait to that point.

00:08:21.500 --> 00:08:24.530 align:middle line:84%
And that's unfortunate,
what most people do.

00:08:24.530 --> 00:08:27.080 align:middle line:84%
>> The other very simple
thing that you say here,

00:08:27.080 --> 00:08:28.670 align:middle line:90%
which is very, very shocking--

00:08:28.670 --> 00:08:29.510 align:middle line:90%
>> What?

00:08:29.510 --> 00:08:32.270 align:middle line:90%
>> Don't answer the phone.

00:08:32.270 --> 00:08:34.610 align:middle line:84%
>> It's so simple,
and it's so hard.

00:08:34.610 --> 00:08:36.132 align:middle line:84%
The phone rings,
and the first thing

00:08:36.132 --> 00:08:38.090 align:middle line:84%
you do-- you could be in
a meeting or whatever.

00:08:38.090 --> 00:08:39.230 align:middle line:90%
And you pick it up.

00:08:39.230 --> 00:08:42.590 align:middle line:84%
The phone takes priority already
over everything, it seems.

00:08:42.590 --> 00:08:45.290 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I say,
don't answer the phone.

00:08:45.290 --> 00:08:48.358 align:middle line:84%
It is so efficient
to just let it ring.

00:08:48.358 --> 00:08:49.400 align:middle line:90%
Get an answering service.

00:08:49.400 --> 00:08:51.442 align:middle line:84%
Everybody has some kind
of voicemail or whatever.

00:08:51.442 --> 00:08:53.420 align:middle line:90%
Let that work for you.

00:08:53.420 --> 00:08:54.350 align:middle line:90%
Use that.

00:08:54.350 --> 00:08:56.030 align:middle line:84%
Let it work for you,
and call back when

00:08:56.030 --> 00:08:57.870 align:middle line:90%
you're ready to talk to them.

00:08:57.870 --> 00:08:58.670 align:middle line:90%
Set aside a time--

00:08:58.670 --> 00:09:00.308 align:middle line:84%
>> Or call back when they're
not home and you can talk

00:09:00.308 --> 00:09:00.350 align:middle line:90%
to their voicemail.

00:09:00.350 --> 00:09:02.350 align:middle line:84%
>> That's why you can
leave the -- that's right.

00:09:02.350 --> 00:09:03.650 align:middle line:90%
That's really an efficient way.

00:09:03.650 --> 00:09:04.695 align:middle line:90%
I use that all the time.

00:09:04.695 --> 00:09:06.320 align:middle line:84%
Because sometimes I
call intentionally,

00:09:06.320 --> 00:09:08.360 align:middle line:84%
like you said, knowing
they're probably not there.

00:09:08.360 --> 00:09:09.350 align:middle line:90%
But I can leave the answer.

00:09:09.350 --> 00:09:11.308 align:middle line:84%
And you don't have to
have a long conversation.

00:09:11.308 --> 00:09:13.010 align:middle line:84%
It's easier to say
no on the phone.

00:09:13.010 --> 00:09:15.830 align:middle line:84%
You don't want to talk to
them directly, that's OK.

00:09:15.830 --> 00:09:18.350 align:middle line:84%
But absolutely
use the technology

00:09:18.350 --> 00:09:20.840 align:middle line:90%
to help you to manage your time.

00:09:20.840 --> 00:09:23.750 align:middle line:84%
Time management is so important
to eliminating that stress,

00:09:23.750 --> 00:09:24.620 align:middle line:90%
that factor there.

00:09:24.620 --> 00:09:27.380 align:middle line:84%
If you understand some of the
tips that are really simple,

00:09:27.380 --> 00:09:29.990 align:middle line:84%
like not answering the
phone, like closing your door

00:09:29.990 --> 00:09:32.310 align:middle line:84%
if you're at work and you
don't want to deal with it--

00:09:32.310 --> 00:09:33.560 align:middle line:90%
there's so many little things.

00:09:33.560 --> 00:09:36.113 align:middle line:84%
You can do put a sign
up-- "work in progress."

00:09:36.113 --> 00:09:38.030 align:middle line:84%
Or "I'll take appointments
at a certain time."

00:09:38.030 --> 00:09:39.683 align:middle line:90%
You control your life.

00:09:39.683 --> 00:09:40.600 align:middle line:90%
See, that's the thing.

00:09:40.600 --> 00:09:42.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, the telephone is
a very insistent thing.

00:09:42.800 --> 00:09:46.580 align:middle line:84%
One of my pet peeves has always
been in a department store--

00:09:46.580 --> 00:09:49.700 align:middle line:84%
when someone is waiting
on me and the phone rings,

00:09:49.700 --> 00:09:51.480 align:middle line:90%
they will answer the phone be--

00:09:51.480 --> 00:09:52.280 align:middle line:90%
>> While-- right.

00:09:52.280 --> 00:09:53.080 align:middle line:90%
And you're there.

00:09:53.080 --> 00:09:54.180 align:middle line:90%
>> And I'm here.

00:09:54.180 --> 00:09:54.980 align:middle line:90%
>> I know.

00:09:54.980 --> 00:09:55.780 align:middle line:90%
It does bother me.

00:09:55.780 --> 00:09:57.280 align:middle line:84%
>> I mean, the
phone is a tyrant.

00:09:57.280 --> 00:09:58.080 align:middle line:90%
>> It is.

00:09:58.080 --> 00:09:58.950 align:middle line:90%
It really is.

00:09:58.950 --> 00:10:01.100 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's a blessing, but
it's also almost a curse,

00:10:01.100 --> 00:10:01.900 align:middle line:90%
sometimes.

00:10:01.900 --> 00:10:02.870 align:middle line:90%
You're exactly right.

00:10:02.870 --> 00:10:04.453 align:middle line:84%
And that's why we
have to get control.

00:10:04.453 --> 00:10:06.170 align:middle line:90%
Turn off the ringer.

00:10:06.170 --> 00:10:08.630 align:middle line:84%
We don't want-- we're so
fearful, I guess, I don't know,

00:10:08.630 --> 00:10:10.010 align:middle line:84%
that we're going to miss
something important?

00:10:10.010 --> 00:10:10.100 align:middle line:84%
>> Are we going
to miss something?

00:10:10.100 --> 00:10:10.250 align:middle line:90%
>> I know.

00:10:10.250 --> 00:10:12.020 align:middle line:90%
We're going to miss something.

00:10:12.020 --> 00:10:14.600 align:middle line:84%
But without that, if
we just continually--

00:10:14.600 --> 00:10:15.813 align:middle line:90%
the crisis comes up.

00:10:15.813 --> 00:10:17.480 align:middle line:84%
And what I remember--
a phrase, I think.

00:10:17.480 --> 00:10:22.190 align:middle line:84%
It was something like, why
make your emergency my crisis?

00:10:22.190 --> 00:10:23.095 align:middle line:90%
It's not my issue.

00:10:23.095 --> 00:10:25.220 align:middle line:84%
If you don't pick up the
phone, it's not your issue

00:10:25.220 --> 00:10:26.762 align:middle line:84%
until you know what
the situation is.

00:10:26.762 --> 00:10:29.310 align:middle line:84%
So it's so important
to just try it.

00:10:29.310 --> 00:10:30.460 align:middle line:90%
>> Say that again?

00:10:30.460 --> 00:10:31.370 align:middle line:90%
Don't make what?

00:10:31.370 --> 00:10:33.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Your emergency, my crisis.

00:10:33.650 --> 00:10:37.160 align:middle line:84%
Suddenly, whatever your
demands are becomes my crisis.

00:10:37.160 --> 00:10:40.010 align:middle line:84%
But I don't have to pick up the
phone, and it won't be mine.

00:10:40.010 --> 00:10:40.810 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:10:40.810 --> 00:10:43.100 align:middle line:84%
>> At least you can delay
it until you're better able

00:10:43.100 --> 00:10:43.900 align:middle line:90%
to handle--

00:10:43.900 --> 00:10:44.270 align:middle line:90%
>> To handle it.

00:10:44.270 --> 00:10:45.080 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:10:45.080 --> 00:10:45.320 align:middle line:90%
>> Sometimes, right?

00:10:45.320 --> 00:10:45.400 align:middle line:90%
To--

00:10:45.400 --> 00:10:46.430 align:middle line:90%
>> In the time that you want to.

00:10:46.430 --> 00:10:47.230 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:10:47.230 --> 00:10:49.520 align:middle line:84%
>> These are all such
practical things.

00:10:49.520 --> 00:10:51.000 align:middle line:84%
I was really
impressed with them.

00:10:51.000 --> 00:10:51.800 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:10:51.800 --> 00:10:53.250 align:middle line:90%
And they're very simple.

00:10:53.250 --> 00:10:54.050 align:middle line:90%
>> Very simple.

00:10:54.050 --> 00:10:56.040 align:middle line:84%
But I think everything
that's good is simple.

00:10:56.040 --> 00:10:56.840 align:middle line:90%
>> It is.

00:10:56.840 --> 00:10:57.350 align:middle line:90%
It is.

00:10:57.350 --> 00:10:58.183 align:middle line:90%
>> It's really good.

