00:11:40.400 --> 00:11:41.420 align:middle line:90%
Why am I not doing it?

00:11:41.420 --> 00:11:43.680 align:middle line:84%
Because we need someone
like you to remind us.

00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:44.480 align:middle line:90%
That's why.

00:11:44.480 --> 00:11:46.280 align:middle line:90%
>> I think that's so true.

00:11:46.280 --> 00:11:49.070 align:middle line:10%
Most people that
are doing anything

00:11:49.070 --> 00:11:51.380 align:middle line:10%
have heard the
fundamental principles

00:11:51.380 --> 00:11:54.170 align:middle line:10%
of how you can be successful,
how you can manage your time.

00:11:54.170 --> 00:11:55.820 align:middle line:10%
We've heard it at
one time or another.

00:11:55.820 --> 00:11:57.195 align:middle line:84%
But I think what's
real important

00:11:57.195 --> 00:12:00.080 align:middle line:84%
for me is that people
have to hear it

00:12:00.080 --> 00:12:01.220 align:middle line:90%
when they're ready for it.

00:12:01.220 --> 00:12:03.178 align:middle line:84%
Because we're in different
stages all the time.

00:12:03.178 --> 00:12:04.700 align:middle line:90%
We're in different situations.

00:12:04.700 --> 00:12:06.650 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes I may
hear it at a point

00:12:06.650 --> 00:12:08.480 align:middle line:84%
where it just really
doesn't apply.

00:12:08.480 --> 00:12:11.120 align:middle line:84%
Or later, I'll hear the same
thing and it's like, oh,

00:12:11.120 --> 00:12:11.960 align:middle line:90%
you hear it.

00:12:11.960 --> 00:12:13.963 align:middle line:90%
You finally really hear it.

00:12:13.963 --> 00:12:15.005 align:middle line:90%
And so I think it's that.

00:12:15.005 --> 00:12:17.110 align:middle line:84%
It's that you need
to be reminded.

00:12:17.110 --> 00:12:18.110 align:middle line:90%
It's just like exercise.

00:12:18.110 --> 00:12:19.490 align:middle line:84%
You get up and you
get into the groove,

00:12:19.490 --> 00:12:20.990 align:middle line:84%
and you do it really
well for a while,

00:12:20.990 --> 00:12:22.130 align:middle line:90%
and then you kind of slack off.

00:12:22.130 --> 00:12:23.000 align:middle line:84%
And you need somebody
to come back--

00:12:23.000 --> 00:12:23.690 align:middle line:90%
"Come on.

00:12:23.690 --> 00:12:24.490 align:middle line:90%
Get up."

00:12:24.490 --> 00:12:25.858 align:middle line:90%
Here's really how you do it.

00:12:25.858 --> 00:12:27.650 align:middle line:84%
And it's a reminder to
get you going again.

00:12:27.650 --> 00:12:28.450 align:middle line:90%
So we need that.

00:12:28.450 --> 00:12:29.343 align:middle line:90%
We all need that.

00:12:29.343 --> 00:12:31.760 align:middle line:84%
>> That's our job, to remind
each other of what we already

00:12:31.760 --> 00:12:32.270 align:middle line:90%
know, right?

00:12:32.270 --> 00:12:32.600 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:12:32.600 --> 00:12:33.400 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:12:33.400 --> 00:12:35.040 align:middle line:84%
Gently and lovingly,
but remind us.

00:12:35.040 --> 00:12:37.550 align:middle line:90%


00:12:37.550 --> 00:12:40.470 align:middle line:84%
>> You go and speak
to huge corporations,

00:12:40.470 --> 00:12:42.990 align:middle line:84%
and you're a keynote speaker
at many organizations.

00:12:42.990 --> 00:12:43.790 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:12:43.790 --> 00:12:46.080 align:middle line:84%
>> What do they ask you
to speak about, mostly?

00:12:46.080 --> 00:12:47.930 align:middle line:84%
>> Mostly, it's
dealing with balance--

00:12:47.930 --> 00:12:50.570 align:middle line:84%
trying to get the balance
in the order in their lives,

00:12:50.570 --> 00:12:51.650 align:middle line:90%
more than anything.

00:12:51.650 --> 00:12:52.718 align:middle line:90%
I mean, and then--

00:12:52.718 --> 00:12:55.010 align:middle line:84%
they do indicate they're
interested in time management,

00:12:55.010 --> 00:12:57.093 align:middle line:84%
and managing the different
things that are coming.

00:12:57.093 --> 00:12:59.670 align:middle line:84%
But the key is juggling all
of these different things.

00:12:59.670 --> 00:13:01.670 align:middle line:84%
Especially with the
downsizing and right-sizing,

00:13:01.670 --> 00:13:04.670 align:middle line:84%
all the trend that's going on
with companies and mergers,

00:13:04.670 --> 00:13:07.460 align:middle line:84%
different mindsets coming
together with corporations.

00:13:07.460 --> 00:13:09.140 align:middle line:90%
How do you mesh these things?

00:13:09.140 --> 00:13:12.080 align:middle line:84%
And different responsibilities,
more responsibilities,

00:13:12.080 --> 00:13:14.507 align:middle line:84%
less employees-- how do
you handle all of that?

00:13:14.507 --> 00:13:15.840 align:middle line:90%
How do you balance those things?

00:13:15.840 --> 00:13:17.632 align:middle line:84%
And that's really what
the demand has been,

00:13:17.632 --> 00:13:18.920 align:middle line:90%
overwhelmingly.

00:13:18.920 --> 00:13:22.160 align:middle line:84%
And it comes back to those
fundamental pieces again--

00:13:22.160 --> 00:13:25.040 align:middle line:84%
the ones that we've heard
but we haven't done.

00:13:25.040 --> 00:13:27.770 align:middle line:84%
Is understanding, even in the
midst of the work environment,

00:13:27.770 --> 00:13:31.340 align:middle line:84%
where you have some limitation
on choosing certain things,

00:13:31.340 --> 00:13:34.340 align:middle line:84%
but understanding what's
the most important thing?

00:13:34.340 --> 00:13:37.060 align:middle line:84%
You have to have some-- make
a list of the many things you

00:13:37.060 --> 00:13:37.130 align:middle line:90%
have.

00:13:37.130 --> 00:13:39.320 align:middle line:84%
>> That, I think, is a very,
very good point that you make

00:13:39.320 --> 00:13:40.120 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:13:40.120 --> 00:13:42.170 align:middle line:84%
You say, "Take time
every day to plan.

00:13:42.170 --> 00:13:46.107 align:middle line:84%
And Robert Schuller once said,
'People don't plan to fail.

00:13:46.107 --> 00:13:46.940 align:middle line:90%
They fail to plan.'"

00:13:46.940 --> 00:13:47.285 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:13:47.285 --> 00:13:48.340 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:13:48.340 --> 00:13:49.800 align:middle line:84%
>> You actually
make a list, right?

00:13:49.800 --> 00:13:50.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Every day.

00:13:50.600 --> 00:13:51.920 align:middle line:84%
I do it on my
computer, actually.

00:13:51.920 --> 00:13:53.003 align:middle line:90%
I have a computer program.

00:13:53.003 --> 00:13:54.680 align:middle line:84%
And again, you need
to use technology

00:13:54.680 --> 00:13:57.320 align:middle line:84%
as much as you can
to shorten your time.

00:13:57.320 --> 00:13:58.910 align:middle line:90%
But every morning--

00:13:58.910 --> 00:14:01.460 align:middle line:84%
I mean, maybe on Saturdays
and Sundays I might slack off.

00:14:01.460 --> 00:14:04.770 align:middle line:84%
But I have a list of
everything that I need to do.

00:14:04.770 --> 00:14:06.170 align:middle line:90%
And then-- here's the key part.

00:14:06.170 --> 00:14:08.030 align:middle line:84%
Because a lot of people make
the list-- and that's good.

00:14:08.030 --> 00:14:09.200 align:middle line:90%
That's the first step.

00:14:09.200 --> 00:14:12.440 align:middle line:84%
But the second is critical--
is to prioritize it.

00:14:12.440 --> 00:14:13.940 align:middle line:84%
Because you can
have a whole list,

00:14:13.940 --> 00:14:16.273 align:middle line:84%
and you put the fun things,
the easy things, at the top.

00:14:16.273 --> 00:14:17.738 align:middle line:84%
And the most
critical component--

00:14:17.738 --> 00:14:19.780 align:middle line:84%
maybe it's something you
really don't want to do.

00:14:19.780 --> 00:14:22.610 align:middle line:84%
It's challenging, it takes more
time, or whatever it might be.

00:14:22.610 --> 00:14:24.020 align:middle line:84%
But it's the most
essential thing

00:14:24.020 --> 00:14:25.520 align:middle line:84%
to get done-- could
be further down.

00:14:25.520 --> 00:14:27.510 align:middle line:84%
If it's not at the
top of the list,

00:14:27.510 --> 00:14:28.520 align:middle line:84%
that's when you're
going to get in trouble.

00:14:28.520 --> 00:14:30.110 align:middle line:84%
And that's when
the stress comes.

00:14:30.110 --> 00:14:31.430 align:middle line:90%
That's when the concern comes.

00:14:31.430 --> 00:14:33.110 align:middle line:84%
And that's when
the panic sets in.

00:14:33.110 --> 00:14:34.790 align:middle line:90%
Because at the end of the day--

00:14:34.790 --> 00:14:37.700 align:middle line:84%
and you've got many things done,
perhaps, but the most important

00:14:37.700 --> 00:14:38.510 align:middle line:90%
is not.

00:14:38.510 --> 00:14:39.770 align:middle line:90%
Real fundamental.

00:14:39.770 --> 00:14:40.940 align:middle line:90%
And people don't do that.

00:14:40.940 --> 00:14:43.460 align:middle line:84%
I remember a story I
heard a long time ago,

00:14:43.460 --> 00:14:45.470 align:middle line:90%
and it's so fitting.

00:14:45.470 --> 00:14:47.270 align:middle line:90%
I guess it happened in the '30s.

00:14:47.270 --> 00:14:50.360 align:middle line:84%
And it was a consultant that
was brought into a company

00:14:50.360 --> 00:14:51.710 align:middle line:90%
to look at the operations.

00:14:51.710 --> 00:14:53.600 align:middle line:84%
They weren't producing
as much as they could,

00:14:53.600 --> 00:14:55.220 align:middle line:90%
or as efficiently as they could.

00:14:55.220 --> 00:14:56.750 align:middle line:84%
So they brought in
this consultant.

00:14:56.750 --> 00:14:59.400 align:middle line:84%
Consultant came and observed
for a couple of days.

00:14:59.400 --> 00:15:01.790 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of that, he
sat down with the executive

00:15:01.790 --> 00:15:03.570 align:middle line:90%
and said, it's real simple.

00:15:03.570 --> 00:15:07.370 align:middle line:84%
You need to just make a
list, prioritize it, start

00:15:07.370 --> 00:15:09.500 align:middle line:84%
at the top, and
unless you absolutely

00:15:09.500 --> 00:15:13.010 align:middle line:84%
have to go to the next thing,
do not move from that first task

00:15:13.010 --> 00:15:14.930 align:middle line:84%
until you can get--
it's completed.

00:15:14.930 --> 00:15:17.270 align:middle line:84%
Well, the manager
or the executive

00:15:17.270 --> 00:15:20.278 align:middle line:84%
said, I'm not going to pay you
what we talked about for this--

00:15:20.278 --> 00:15:22.070 align:middle line:84%
for you to come and
tell me to make a list,

00:15:22.070 --> 00:15:23.660 align:middle line:90%
prioritize it, and follow it?

00:15:23.660 --> 00:15:25.820 align:middle line:90%
So the consultant said, fine.

00:15:25.820 --> 00:15:27.680 align:middle line:90%
Tear up the old agreement.

00:15:27.680 --> 00:15:30.530 align:middle line:84%
Just use this simple
idea for 30 days.

00:15:30.530 --> 00:15:32.660 align:middle line:84%
At the end of that
period, send me a check

00:15:32.660 --> 00:15:34.460 align:middle line:90%
for what you think it's worth.

00:15:34.460 --> 00:15:36.170 align:middle line:84%
Executive said,
OK, we'll do that.

00:15:36.170 --> 00:15:37.400 align:middle line:90%
So he did that.

00:15:37.400 --> 00:15:41.330 align:middle line:84%
At the end of the 30 days, he
sent this consultant $25,000--

00:15:41.330 --> 00:15:42.860 align:middle line:90%
now, this is back in the '30s--

00:15:42.860 --> 00:15:44.720 align:middle line:90%
just for that one idea.

00:15:44.720 --> 00:15:46.710 align:middle line:90%
Because it really is powerful.

00:15:46.710 --> 00:15:49.963 align:middle line:84%
It's simple, but that's what
we need to do to get some order

00:15:49.963 --> 00:15:51.380 align:middle line:84%
and get rid of
some of the stress.

00:15:51.380 --> 00:15:52.797 align:middle line:84%
Because if you
don't get something

00:15:52.797 --> 00:15:54.560 align:middle line:84%
else done that's
not as important,

00:15:54.560 --> 00:15:56.120 align:middle line:90%
you don't feel as bad.

00:15:56.120 --> 00:15:57.260 align:middle line:90%
So it's really simple.

00:15:57.260 --> 00:15:58.060 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:15:58.060 --> 00:16:01.260 align:middle line:84%
I think what we do is, we tend
to do the easy stuff first.

00:16:01.260 --> 00:16:02.323 align:middle line:90%
>> The fun things.

00:16:02.323 --> 00:16:03.240 align:middle line:90%
You call your friends.

00:16:03.240 --> 00:16:04.880 align:middle line:84%
I've got to call my
friend, but you're

00:16:04.880 --> 00:16:06.360 align:middle line:90%
on the phone for 20 minutes.

00:16:06.360 --> 00:16:07.160 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:16:07.160 --> 00:16:08.360 align:middle line:84%
>> So you could
write this-- really,

00:16:08.360 --> 00:16:10.600 align:middle line:84%
you don't have to be so
sophisticated as to put it

00:16:10.600 --> 00:16:11.400 align:middle line:90%
on a computer.

00:16:11.400 --> 00:16:12.710 align:middle line:84%
You could put it on the
back of an envelope.

00:16:12.710 --> 00:16:13.752 align:middle line:90%
>> A piece of-- whatever.

00:16:13.752 --> 00:16:14.700 align:middle line:90%
>> And just put--

00:16:14.700 --> 00:16:18.910 align:middle line:84%
next to what's most
important, put an A or a 1.

00:16:18.910 --> 00:16:19.710 align:middle line:90%
>> A or 1.

00:16:19.710 --> 00:16:20.817 align:middle line:90%
A, B, C. 1, 2, 3.

00:16:20.817 --> 00:16:21.900 align:middle line:90%
There's different systems.

00:16:21.900 --> 00:16:23.170 align:middle line:90%
Whatever works for the person.

00:16:23.170 --> 00:16:24.900 align:middle line:84%
But there's got to
be some semblance of,

00:16:24.900 --> 00:16:25.950 align:middle line:90%
what's a priority?

00:16:25.950 --> 00:16:28.510 align:middle line:84%
Number one, A, has
to be essential.

00:16:28.510 --> 00:16:29.340 align:middle line:90%
It has to get done.

00:16:29.340 --> 00:16:29.910 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:16:29.910 --> 00:16:31.020 align:middle line:90%
It's fundamental-- critical.

00:16:31.020 --> 00:16:31.820 align:middle line:90%
>> And you start.

00:16:31.820 --> 00:16:32.700 align:middle line:90%
>> You start there.

00:16:32.700 --> 00:16:34.240 align:middle line:84%
And then, after you do
that-- because you're

00:16:34.240 --> 00:16:35.400 align:middle line:90%
going to have several things.

00:16:35.400 --> 00:16:37.200 align:middle line:84%
You don't want to have
a long laundry list.

00:16:37.200 --> 00:16:38.527 align:middle line:90%
You need to make it realistic.

00:16:38.527 --> 00:16:40.860 align:middle line:84%
But after you've done that,
you're going to have several

00:16:40.860 --> 00:16:42.780 align:middle line:90%
A's, several B's, several C's.

00:16:42.780 --> 00:16:45.670 align:middle line:84%
Then you need to go back,
even within that category.

00:16:45.670 --> 00:16:48.340 align:middle line:84%
What's the most fundamental
thing that has to be done?

00:16:48.340 --> 00:16:49.560 align:middle line:84%
>> You know what I
found when I do this?

00:16:49.560 --> 00:16:51.040 align:middle line:84%
And I do this every
once in a while.

00:16:51.040 --> 00:16:52.748 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to start
doing it tomorrow.

00:16:52.748 --> 00:16:53.760 align:middle line:90%
>> Good, good.

00:16:53.760 --> 00:16:55.470 align:middle line:84%
>> By the time you
get around to the C,

00:16:55.470 --> 00:16:57.430 align:middle line:84%
sometimes the people
have forgotten about it,

00:16:57.430 --> 00:16:58.900 align:middle line:84%
and you don't have
to do it at all.

00:16:58.900 --> 00:16:59.500 align:middle line:90%
>> That's true.

00:16:59.500 --> 00:17:00.300 align:middle line:90%
That is very true.

00:17:00.300 --> 00:17:01.640 align:middle line:90%
And here's another secret.

00:17:01.640 --> 00:17:02.750 align:middle line:90%
Here's a really good one.

00:17:02.750 --> 00:17:03.917 align:middle line:90%
And I don't do this as well.

00:17:03.917 --> 00:17:05.460 align:middle line:90%
And I'm getting better.

00:17:05.460 --> 00:17:09.390 align:middle line:84%
Is, those C's, or
mini-things, delegate.

00:17:09.390 --> 00:17:11.550 align:middle line:90%
Delegate, delegate, delegate.

00:17:11.550 --> 00:17:12.920 align:middle line:90%
You have this long list.

00:17:12.920 --> 00:17:14.503 align:middle line:84%
There's certain
things you have to do.

00:17:14.503 --> 00:17:18.060 align:middle line:84%
There's many things you really
don't have to do yourself.

00:17:18.060 --> 00:17:21.839 align:middle line:84%
And, yes, I don't give them
out to other people too well.

00:17:21.839 --> 00:17:23.430 align:middle line:90%
But that's what we need to do.

00:17:23.430 --> 00:17:26.160 align:middle line:84%
If there's someone else-- if
you're not the only one that

00:17:26.160 --> 00:17:28.230 align:middle line:90%
has to do it, delegate it.

00:17:28.230 --> 00:17:30.210 align:middle line:84%
That's the rule of
thumb to start with.

00:17:30.210 --> 00:17:32.170 align:middle line:84%
There are some times
you still can do it--

00:17:32.170 --> 00:17:34.440 align:middle line:84%
some things that you could
have someone else do.

00:17:34.440 --> 00:17:37.140 align:middle line:84%
But if you're not the
one that has to do this,

00:17:37.140 --> 00:17:39.000 align:middle line:84%
try to find someone
else to do it.

00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:40.870 align:middle line:90%
That's a really good--

00:17:40.870 --> 00:17:43.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Find somebody who hasn't
learned yet to say no.

00:17:43.710 --> 00:17:44.700 align:middle line:90%
>> That's true.

00:17:44.700 --> 00:17:46.380 align:middle line:84%
That's pretty bad,
but that's true.

00:17:46.380 --> 00:17:47.530 align:middle line:90%
And then the other thing--

00:17:47.530 --> 00:17:48.330 align:middle line:90%
think of this.

00:17:48.330 --> 00:17:50.310 align:middle line:84%
You're really giving
them an opportunity

00:17:50.310 --> 00:17:53.790 align:middle line:84%
to expand their horizons,
to experience this activity.

00:17:53.790 --> 00:17:55.650 align:middle line:84%
Because, truly, they
could be at a point--

00:17:55.650 --> 00:17:57.067 align:middle line:84%
it could be someone
that's working

00:17:57.067 --> 00:17:59.610 align:middle line:84%
for you that you're going to
delegate a responsibility to.

00:17:59.610 --> 00:18:00.300 align:middle line:90%
And they're growing.

00:18:00.300 --> 00:18:01.320 align:middle line:84%
They're learning
from doing this.

00:18:01.320 --> 00:18:03.540 align:middle line:84%
You still have responsibility
when you delegate,

00:18:03.540 --> 00:18:06.090 align:middle line:84%
but you don't actually
devote the time, necessarily,

00:18:06.090 --> 00:18:06.490 align:middle line:90%
to do it.

00:18:06.490 --> 00:18:07.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Phone call.

00:18:07.170 --> 00:18:07.830 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:18:07.830 --> 00:18:09.120 align:middle line:90%
Have someone else to do that.

00:18:09.120 --> 00:18:10.200 align:middle line:90%
And that's so important.

00:18:10.200 --> 00:18:11.783 align:middle line:84%
And you could say--
you can look at it

00:18:11.783 --> 00:18:14.550 align:middle line:84%
as a way of helping other
people grow, which is true.

00:18:14.550 --> 00:18:16.800 align:middle line:84%
So that's another
really strong tip.

00:18:16.800 --> 00:18:20.340 align:middle line:84%
>> I think that it comes down--
especially for women, I think.

00:18:20.340 --> 00:18:22.620 align:middle line:84%
We feel we have to do
everything so perfectly.

00:18:22.620 --> 00:18:24.660 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, that's a good one.

00:18:24.660 --> 00:18:29.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Getting in the car and
driving 6 miles to get

00:18:29.280 --> 00:18:33.690 align:middle line:84%
something that's on sale that
you can buy in your corner

00:18:33.690 --> 00:18:38.140 align:middle line:84%
grocery for $1 more is something
we feel obligated to do when

00:18:38.140 --> 00:18:38.940 align:middle line:90%
we--

00:18:38.940 --> 00:18:41.160 align:middle line:84%
why are we spending
all of that time?

00:18:41.160 --> 00:18:42.175 align:middle line:90%
>> I don't really know.

00:18:42.175 --> 00:18:43.800 align:middle line:84%
>> It's about being
a superwoman again.

00:18:43.800 --> 00:18:44.355 align:middle line:90%
>> It is.

00:18:44.355 --> 00:18:44.970 align:middle line:90%
It is.

00:18:44.970 --> 00:18:47.520 align:middle line:84%
And here's another piece that
goes right along with that--

00:18:47.520 --> 00:18:52.860 align:middle line:84%
is that we don't either feel we
can, or whatever the reason is,

00:18:52.860 --> 00:18:54.990 align:middle line:84%
to bring people--
help into the house--

00:18:54.990 --> 00:18:55.950 align:middle line:90%
to the household.

00:18:55.950 --> 00:18:58.530 align:middle line:84%
Now, some people say, well,
I really can't afford this.

00:18:58.530 --> 00:19:00.840 align:middle line:84%
But it's almost-- if you're
working and trying to run

00:19:00.840 --> 00:19:03.140 align:middle line:84%
a household, you almost
cannot afford to do this.

00:19:03.140 --> 00:19:07.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Or a simple thing like taking
the shirts out of the laundry,

00:19:07.710 --> 00:19:09.370 align:middle line:84%
and paying $1 apiece
to have them done.

00:19:09.370 --> 00:19:10.170 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:19:10.170 --> 00:19:10.800 align:middle line:90%
>> Instead of you trying to--

00:19:10.800 --> 00:19:10.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Instead of--

00:19:10.990 --> 00:19:11.450 align:middle line:90%
>> --sit there and iron them.

00:19:11.450 --> 00:19:12.660 align:middle line:84%
>> --figuring you've
got to iron them.

00:19:12.660 --> 00:19:13.230 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:19:13.230 --> 00:19:13.770 align:middle line:90%
That's correct.

00:19:13.770 --> 00:19:13.890 align:middle line:90%
That's--

00:19:13.890 --> 00:19:15.500 align:middle line:84%
>> Or even wash them
and shake them out.

00:19:15.500 --> 00:19:16.300 align:middle line:90%
>> Mhm.

00:19:16.300 --> 00:19:17.393 align:middle line:90%
That is so true.

00:19:17.393 --> 00:19:18.810 align:middle line:84%
And you need to
free up yourself--

00:19:18.810 --> 00:19:21.712 align:middle line:84%
there's some things you need
to do, and you want to do.

00:19:21.712 --> 00:19:23.920 align:middle line:84%
That you want to have a
connection with the children.

00:19:23.920 --> 00:19:24.870 align:middle line:90%
You want to do certain things.

00:19:24.870 --> 00:19:27.287 align:middle line:84%
You don't necessarily want to
give up all of those things.

00:19:27.287 --> 00:19:28.460 align:middle line:90%
But there are some things--

00:19:28.460 --> 00:19:30.502 align:middle line:84%
and I remember someone--
distinctly-- telling me,

00:19:30.502 --> 00:19:33.210 align:middle line:84%
Celeste, with the kind
of schedule you have,

00:19:33.210 --> 00:19:35.700 align:middle line:84%
and the running around, you
cannot afford to be doing

00:19:35.700 --> 00:19:38.580 align:middle line:84%
housecleaning all
day long on Saturday.

00:19:38.580 --> 00:19:41.340 align:middle line:84%
You need to have a point where
you can rest and rejuvenate.

00:19:41.340 --> 00:19:44.430 align:middle line:84%
And you can't do that if you're
always working, or always doing

00:19:44.430 --> 00:19:45.240 align:middle line:90%
something.

00:19:45.240 --> 00:19:47.530 align:middle line:90%
Then some people you can hire.

00:19:47.530 --> 00:19:48.330 align:middle line:90%
It's worth it.

00:19:48.330 --> 00:19:49.740 align:middle line:90%
Turn down that dinner.

00:19:49.740 --> 00:19:53.010 align:middle line:84%
Instead of spending $25
there, or $50 that week--

00:19:53.010 --> 00:19:55.140 align:middle line:84%
and pay someone to come
and do something for you.

00:19:55.140 --> 00:19:56.560 align:middle line:90%
It's invaluable.

00:19:56.560 --> 00:19:57.360 align:middle line:90%
It really is.

00:19:57.360 --> 00:19:58.530 align:middle line:90%
>> We feel guilty.

00:19:58.530 --> 00:19:59.490 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, that's true.

00:19:59.490 --> 00:20:00.750 align:middle line:84%
But we're going to have
to deal with our guilt,

00:20:00.750 --> 00:20:02.190 align:middle line:84%
or we're going to
deal with the stress--

00:20:02.190 --> 00:20:03.065 align:middle line:90%
the remnants of that.

00:20:03.065 --> 00:20:04.560 align:middle line:90%
And that's really not healthy.

00:20:04.560 --> 00:20:07.817 align:middle line:84%
Because ultimately, if we get
burnt out, as we said before,

00:20:07.817 --> 00:20:09.900 align:middle line:84%
and you get to the point
where you can't function,

00:20:09.900 --> 00:20:12.270 align:middle line:84%
that's worse than having someone
else to come in and do it.

00:20:12.270 --> 00:20:13.290 align:middle line:90%
>> Somebody cleans every day.

00:20:13.290 --> 00:20:13.800 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:20:13.800 --> 00:20:14.600 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:20:14.600 --> 00:20:16.260 align:middle line:84%
And you don't want
to go out that way.

00:20:16.260 --> 00:20:19.020 align:middle line:84%
Again, I've seen many
people that I know,

00:20:19.020 --> 00:20:21.690 align:middle line:84%
or people I've heard
of, that wait until they

00:20:21.690 --> 00:20:25.140 align:middle line:84%
get some terminal illness,
or some crisis that they've

00:20:25.140 --> 00:20:28.440 align:middle line:84%
heard about, or that they're
experiencing indirectly,

00:20:28.440 --> 00:20:32.100 align:middle line:84%
or something comes up before
they pay attention, and realize

00:20:32.100 --> 00:20:35.220 align:middle line:84%
that they must take
this time along the way

00:20:35.220 --> 00:20:36.970 align:middle line:90%
to have-- to reduce the stress.

00:20:36.970 --> 00:20:37.770 align:middle line:90%
Stress is a killer.

00:20:37.770 --> 00:20:40.740 align:middle line:84%
Do you know, we have incredible
heart attack rate-- just

00:20:40.740 --> 00:20:43.170 align:middle line:90%
continues to go up every year.

00:20:43.170 --> 00:20:46.740 align:middle line:84%
The drugs, and amphetamines, and
the different barbiturates that

00:20:46.740 --> 00:20:49.560 align:middle line:90%
are prescribed are incredible--

00:20:49.560 --> 00:20:51.600 align:middle line:84%
that we continue
to do these things,

00:20:51.600 --> 00:20:54.160 align:middle line:84%
just pacifying ourselves,
when in essence,

00:20:54.160 --> 00:20:56.460 align:middle line:84%
if we just did the fundamental
things of taking time

00:20:56.460 --> 00:20:58.230 align:middle line:84%
to rejuvenate, taking
time to be quiet.

00:20:58.230 --> 00:20:59.340 align:middle line:90%
Don't answer that phone.

00:20:59.340 --> 00:21:00.863 align:middle line:90%
Take that hour for yourself.

00:21:00.863 --> 00:21:02.280 align:middle line:84%
Make an appointment
with yourself.

00:21:02.280 --> 00:21:03.992 align:middle line:90%
Put it in the date book.

00:21:03.992 --> 00:21:06.450 align:middle line:84%
>> There's so many things in
here that we could talk about,

00:21:06.450 --> 00:21:08.940 align:middle line:84%
but that was a very
good suggestion, too--

00:21:08.940 --> 00:21:11.240 align:middle line:84%
when you make out your
calendar for the month,

00:21:11.240 --> 00:21:14.330 align:middle line:84%
to actually put some
time in for yourself,

00:21:14.330 --> 00:21:15.620 align:middle line:90%
say, from 2:00 to 4:00.

00:21:15.620 --> 00:21:17.060 align:middle line:90%
And make up somebody's name.

00:21:17.060 --> 00:21:18.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Whoever you want.

00:21:18.310 --> 00:21:20.720 align:middle line:90%
And keep that appointment.

00:21:20.720 --> 00:21:23.010 align:middle line:84%
And do not-- treat it
like an appointment.

00:21:23.010 --> 00:21:23.810 align:middle line:90%
Because it is.

00:21:23.810 --> 00:21:24.680 align:middle line:90%
And it's so important.

00:21:24.680 --> 00:21:27.170 align:middle line:84%
You're as important as any
other appointment that you have.

00:21:27.170 --> 00:21:29.090 align:middle line:90%
You're more important, actually.

00:21:29.090 --> 00:21:30.560 align:middle line:90%
And so without that--

00:21:30.560 --> 00:21:31.827 align:middle line:90%
go to the movies.

00:21:31.827 --> 00:21:32.660 align:middle line:90%
Do the things that--

00:21:32.660 --> 00:21:33.702 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I didn't do that.

00:21:33.702 --> 00:21:35.450 align:middle line:90%
I had gotten so away from that.

00:21:35.450 --> 00:21:37.310 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the things
that I really enjoyed.

00:21:37.310 --> 00:21:38.600 align:middle line:90%
And I worked in--

00:21:38.600 --> 00:21:39.800 align:middle line:90%
I'm in business for myself.

00:21:39.800 --> 00:21:41.900 align:middle line:90%
And people often want to do.

00:21:41.900 --> 00:21:43.640 align:middle line:84%
We want to be able
to have our own time.

00:21:43.640 --> 00:21:45.980 align:middle line:84%
Well, you get into working
for yourself and you realize,

00:21:45.980 --> 00:21:47.480 align:middle line:84%
you really don't
have a lot of time,

00:21:47.480 --> 00:21:49.188 align:middle line:84%
because everything is
dependent upon you.

00:21:49.188 --> 00:21:53.470 align:middle line:84%
But you must build in
that time to remember

00:21:53.470 --> 00:21:56.360 align:middle line:84%
why you did this in the
beginning, and to enjoy life--

00:21:56.360 --> 00:21:57.810 align:middle line:90%
to really make a difference.

00:21:57.810 --> 00:22:00.440 align:middle line:84%
And so I really urge
people to put them

00:22:00.440 --> 00:22:01.910 align:middle line:90%
in their schedule-- at the top.

